<br>
I think that 3-5k for a mount is a rather reasonable figure. Seeing as how there will possibly be a limited number of mounts in the game:<br>
<br>
Will anyone ever need another once they have 1? Do mounts get old and die? Doubtful. Once you have one, you wont ever need another one again. Unless you feel like going for a different "look". Even then, how many people are there on a server? 3000? 4000? --<br>
<br>
lets say 2% of the population of a server is CHs with Management 4. Lets also say that they are 4000 people on a server. That means that there are 80 CHs on any server who can train mounts. If each trainer trained an equal share, that would mean each would train 50 mounts. 50 X 5000 = 250,000 credits.<br>
<br>
How much is a large house?<br>
<br>
250,000 for training 50 mounts doesnt seem like such a ripoff. Scpecially since once the major portion of the server is done getting a mount you will see very litle in the way of business again.<br>
<br>
And then when vehicles come in to the game ... who's going to ride a dewback when you can zip along on a swoop bike or in a speeder?<br>
<br>
take what you can get, while you can get it.. once the charm wears off, it will be a rare enough trade.<br>
